      boolean breakTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks​(T unit)
      Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
      In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
      If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
      Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

      'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
      ResourcePreemptionPolicy breakTaskPreemptionPolicy​(T unit)
      Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
      NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
      TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

      'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends

        public boolean destroyExcessUnits
        [actual for capacity defined directly, by schedule or by on/off schedule]
        If true, once the capacity of pool decreases, all the excess units will be destroyed (and removed from their population, if any), so for the next capacity recovery, brand new units will be created.
        If false, units are retained alive when the capacity of pool decreases (this is like their shift ends) and reactivated when capacity recovers

        Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.

        If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.

        'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.

      • maintenanceTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks

        public boolean maintenanceTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks​(T unit)
        Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
        In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
        If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
        Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

        'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.

      • onUnitStateChange

        public void onUnitStateChange​(T unit,
                              boolean busy,
                              ResourceTaskType type,
                              com.anylogic.engine.Agent agent,
                              ResourceTask task)
        Code executed when new unit changes its activity.

        Parameter:
        T unit - resource unit.
        boolean busy - true if the unit is busy (this doesn't mean that it was idle before), false if idle.
        ResourceTaskType type - type of task, if unit is busy, one of: TASK_ENTITY, TASK_END_OF_SHIFT, TASK_WRAP_UP, TASK_BREAK, TASK_REPAIR, TASK_MAINTENANCE, TASK_CUSTOM constants from ResourceTaskType option list.
        Agent agent - agent associated with this unit's task. Actual for TASK_ENTITY type (where it is the agent possessing the unit) and for TASK_WRAP_UP (agent which previously used this unit and has recently released it).
        ResourceTask task - task descriptor, this can be used in case for TASK_CUSTOM type: there will be a reference to ResourceTask block which represents current task of the unit.

      • setShiftGroupCapacity

        public void setShiftGroupCapacity​(int id,
                                  int capacity)
        Sets new size of shift group.
        Doesn't kill excess resource units. Instead assigns Out-of-shift task to them (idle units are the first to be pushed to Out-of-shift, the next are units with less-priority tasks).
        Note that depending on priority/preemption settings of Out-of-shift task, some units may still be busy with their current tasks (they will go out-of-shift when possible).

        If this resource pool works with schedule then the given capacity will be overridden on the next schedule-based capacity change.
        If capacity is "defined directly", it is possible to call set_capacity() function as well.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of shift group (1, 2, 3...)
        capacity - new size of shift group
